s"},"body":"[~zhill], can you confirm for us that the euca-detach-volume workaround is valid only prior to the reboot or even after a non-clean reboot occurs you can still recover?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=dstagnaro","name":"dstagnaro","key":"dstagnaro","accountId":"557058:ab9ac2db-0ce9-444b-b209-d57d16ac0e46","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/47244def11603caaf3cf61fc30c36997?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Ddstagnaro%26avatarId%3D11000%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/47244def11603caaf3cf61fc30c36997?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Ddstagnaro%26avatarId%3D11000%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/47244def11603caaf3cf61fc30c36997?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Ddstagnaro%26avatarId%3D11000%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/47244def11603caaf3cf61fc30c36997?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Ddstagnaro%26avatarId%3D11000%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Darren Stagnaro","active":false,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2013-02-14T21:32:43.499-0600","updated":"2013-02-14T21:32:43.499-0600"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/19208/comment/39694","id":"39694","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=shashi","name":"shashi","key":"shashi","accountId":"557058:cc7ee5dc-1d4f-46c5-8068-6ae350275ba6","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a22dc501b633d766a04aac00a6f07d91?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dshashi%26avatarId%3D11700%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a22dc501b633d766a04aac00a6f07d91?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dshashi%26avatarId%3D11700%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a22dc501b633d766a04aac00a6f07d91?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dshashi%26avatarId%3D11700%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a22dc501b633d766a04aac00a6f07d91?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dshashi%26avatarId%3D11700%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Shashi Mysore","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"[~zhill], Is there any risk of data corruption? \n\nWhat steps should an administrator follow prior to / after an intended restart of the SC?\n\nWhat steps should an administrator follow after an unintended restart of the SC?\n\nLastly, we should add this to the list of known issues, with the workaround. May be [~dstagnaro] is already working on this and related communication.\n\nThanks,\n-Shashi.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=shashi","name":"shashi","key":"shashi","accountId":"557058:cc7ee5dc-1d4f-46c5-8068-6ae350275ba6","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a22dc501b633d766a04aac00a6f07d91?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dshashi%26avatarId%3D11700%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a22dc501b633d766a04aac00a6f07d91?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dshashi%26avatarId%3D11700%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a22dc501b633d766a04aac00a6f07d91?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dshashi%26avatarId%3D11700%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a22dc501b633d766a04aac00a6f07d91?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dshashi%26avatarId%3D11700%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Shashi Mysore","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2013-02-14T22:25:44.814-0600","updated":"2013-02-14T22:25:44.814-0600"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/19208/comment/39716","id":"39716","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=zhill","name":"zhill","key":"zhill","accountId":"557058:70b4b768-eb1f-43a3-a225-3353d0fe3f56","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Zach Hill","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"[~dstagnaro], the euca-detach-volume workaround definitely works after the reboot. You can do:\nreboot (clean or not)\ndetach-vols\nre-attach-vols\n\nAnd the system should be good to go with all attachements restored properly.\n\n[~shashi], the data will not be corrupted that is already on the disk, but the instance may leave the volume in an inconsistent state because some writes made it to disk and others didn't. This may leave an inconsistent state, but existing data will not be corrupted. This is possible even if this particular bug did not exist. The NC (client) will continue trying to write data, in particular the VM on the NC does not see a failure immediately on a reboot, it will still find data due to caching on the NC and in the instance. At some point if the connection is not restored and the caches are not flushed to the volume, then the VM will put the FS in a read-only mode. Reads will then start to fail as well.\n\nThe risk that this bug poses is that the volume will not be automatically reconnected after restart. I am testing this today to be sure that on a correct restart that the volumes are re-attached correctly. This will be a question of how iSCSI itself handles a disconnect and reconnect.\n\nI'll update with more info later today.\n\nFor an intended restart of the SC: there should be no volumes attached to any instance in that cluster. That ensures that volumes are consistent and instances will not see io errors.\n\nFor unintended restart (i.e. power failure): when the SC comes back up, detach each volume and re-attach it to the instance via (euca-detach-vol and euca-attach-vol). I need to determine if the admin can do this for all users or if each user would have to do this individually.\n\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=zhill","name":"zhill","key":"zhill","accountId":"557058:70b4b768-eb1f-43a3-a225-3353d0fe3f56","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Zach Hill","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2013-02-15T12:33:10.059-0600","updated":"2013-02-15T12:33:10.059-0600"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/19208/comment/39932","id":"39932","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=zhill","name":"zhill","key":"zhill","accountId":"557058:70b4b768-eb1f-43a3-a225-3353d0fe3f56","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Zach Hill","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Committed to maint/3.2/testing with commit id: aa8185b7e86065adcef09019204f2b073365e5fc\r\n\r\nDuring SC startup in OverlayManager it will scan the DB and attempt to re-export any volumes that were exported (had iscsi targets) on last shutdown. The decision is made based on the presence of a loopback device name in the DB. The reload process will restore loopbacks, assign new ones if the previous is taken by another resource, and ensure that LVM LVs are enabled and iSCSI targets reconstructed. If volume is already exported (i.e. just a service restart instead of a machine reboot), then the process cleanly leaves existing resources untouched.\r\n    \r\nAlso adds many INFO level log messages to track process during startup. Grep for 'SC Reload' in the cloud-output.log to see the process.\r\n\r\nTo TEST (easiest in a remote-SC config):\r\n1. Run instance\r\n2. Attach volume to instance.\r\n3. Check losetup -a and tgtadm --lld iscsi -m target -o show on SC. Should see a single loopback and target.\r\n4. Reboot SC\r\n5. Repeat #3 and ensure that output is the same.\r\n6. Do service eucalyptus-cloud restart to verify that after service restarts that output from #3 is unchanged.\r\n\r\nTo test loopback re-assignment:\r\n1. Same as above (steps 1-5), but before reboot, insert 'losetup -f <somefile>' in the /etc/init.d/eucalyptus-cloud script as the first executed line. This will cause the previous loop0 to be used and will force SC to remap loopbacks on reload.\r\n2. After reboot verify that iscsi target is fully functional and NC can read/write to volume.\r\n\r\n\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=zhill","name":"zhill","key":"zhill","accountId":"557058:70b4b768-eb1f-43a3-a225-3353d0fe3f56","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/239165321c2f152424c9be883721791a?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dzhill%26avatarId%3D10406%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Zach Hill","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2013-02-19T20:33:17.744-0600","updated":"2013-02-19T20:33:17.744-0600"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/19208/comment/42267","id":"42267","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=mclark","name":"mclark","key":"mclark","accountId":"557058:9b68e4d6-90d8-47d3-9c86-519770009164","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/4227b07e7ea0ea725670fc4e987ed04d?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/4227b07e7ea0ea725670fc4e987ed04d?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/4227b07e7ea0ea725670fc4e987ed04d?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/4227b07e7ea0ea725670fc4e987ed04d?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Matt Clark","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Wrote the following eutester script to test this in continuous automation. The test runs the script in a multi-cluster/multi-node environment and tests for volume+snapshot create, use and state before and after an SC reboot against all storage backends. This test has run roughly 30 times since against 3.2.2 and passed against overlay. \r\neutester/testcases/cloud_user/ebs/ebs_persistance_tests.py ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassia